      <div class="stack-lg">
        <p class="t-lead t-pretty"><em>Social seeing</em> notices what is broken in the structures around us — patterns, institutions, the inheritances we did not choose. It is sharp and useful, often urgent. It can also become a permanent posture, where everything is the world's fault and nothing is yours to feel.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty"><em>Soul seeing</em> notices what is real beneath appearance — meaning, presence, the slow thread that keeps running through everything. It is spacious. It is rarely in a hurry. It can also drift away from the body if no one calls it back down.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty"><em>Human seeing</em> is the most intimate. It notices what you are actually like — your fears, your softness, your protections, the body you have been carrying. It is the layer that is easiest to skip, because it asks you to feel what you have not yet felt.</p>
        <p class="t-body t-pretty">Wholeness lives where the three meet. None of them was the whole answer; together, they were never separate.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section fade-up">
